					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I've been playing with bank switching with MMC1. I have two 8k CHR banks in my ROM. I set the control register to 8k mode. However, the numbering system appears to be the same as 4k mode, because I only successfully loaded my second CHR bank when I selected chr bank "2". I would have expected "1." The PRG bank selection register appears to be numbered 0, 1 for my two PRG banks; the chr bank selection appears to be numbered 0, 2 for my two CHR banks.  Any idea why this is?  Perhaps I am not serializing my writes correctly (reset + 5 writes is what I am doing to each reg).</div>

