				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">A good use for the 4K mode is to keep the sprites of the player, items, etc always mapped while you switch the background tiles depending on the level being played.
<br />
<br />Of course that there are sprites specific to certain levels, and if you can't fit all of them in the same 4KB, you'll need to either have few different 4KB sprite banks (as long as there are less of them than background banks it's still a gain) or include the level-specific sprites in the background side and use 8x16 sprites.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

